rated workflow combines with a “rollupthesleeves” approach towards fundamental research to fuel an environment of original thinking investment philosophy gardner lewis focuses on transformational change where fundamental research and riskadvantaged positioning can drive favorable outcomes transformational change companies experiencing a catalyst acting as a force to drive growth or unlock value riskadvantaged we seek investment opportunities with attractive upside potential and limited or muted downside risk research since the firm’s inception gardner lewis has been dedicated to fundamentally researched investing  we believe that fundamental work uncovers opportunity and identifies risk fundamental indepth work driven by the bottomup analysis of each opportunity  the potential of each idea is evaluated from a financial and strategic perspective and the thesis is scrutinized rigorously before and during each investment integrated approach we  believe in traders analysts and portfolio managers working together without compartmentalization  our integrated “team” philosophy fuels original thinking variant perception what is it that we understand about this opportunity that differs from the consensus view investment strategies we offer our clients a number of investment options each with a different focus merger arbitrage • pure merger arbitrage • low volatility • uncorrelated   seeks to produce consistent uncorrelated returns with low volatility by investing in mergers and acquisitions  all deals are fundamentally researched and analyzed from a strategic regulatory financial and stakeholder perspective  we believe our strict deal criteria and disciplined risk controls have allowed us to consistently deliver attractive riskadjusted outcomes across various market cycles event driven • merger arbitrage  special situations • full capital structure • hard  soft catalyst   seeks to dynamically allocate capital across hard and soft catalyst opportunity sets  the strategy attempts to pursue merger arbitrage  special situations throughout the capital structure  the preference is for convex return profiles focused on limiting downside while providing attractive upside potential in every investment  the strategy focuses on capital structure liquidity and riskadjusted return analysis within each event events may be either positive or negative including but not limited to corporate actions recapitalizations reorganization change in industry dynamics andor corporate strategy change equity • longshort • long only • private   seeks to invest in fundamentally advantaged companies effecting disruptive innovation in an industry and those that are undergoing positive change as the result of one or more catalysts acting as a force to drive growth or unlock potential enter name enter email submitting form the server encountered an error form received submit message enter your message enter phone number our history gardner lewis asset management was founded in april  by w whitfield gardner and john l lewis iv   the firm is rooted in the belief that a “rollupthesleeves” approach to investing is the best way to uncover unrecognized opportunities since its inception the firm has been privatelyowned and maintains independence from any outside business affiliations or joint ventures  gardner lewis is based in the brandywine valley with its office located in chadds ford pennsylvania   our firm fosters a team environment to provide the highest level of operational expertise and service to our clients  from the beginning gardner lewis has valued a distinctive firm culture and has focused on pursuing favorable investment outcomes through a process that is differentiated and consistent we believe these factors are integral to the value we offer our clients contact us our offices are located in historic chadds ford pennsylvania convenient to the wilmington delaware amtrak train station between ny and washington dc the philadelphia international airport and the cit